{"body": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"installing-pystep\">\n<h1>1.2. Installing pySTEP<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#installing-pystep\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h1>\n<p>Since version 1.3.0, pySTEP no more relies on a list of scripts parametrized by the settings.py file.\nIt consists of a library build with the distutils framework.</p>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"pre-requisite\">\n<h2>1.2.1. Pre-requisite<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#pre-requisite\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>Unlike most Python software, pySTEP required a C compiler to be present on the system.\nThis is due to the fact of using Cython to improve speed.\nSo, you have to install Cython (<a class=\"reference external\" href=\"http://docs.cython.org/src/quickstart/install.html\">http://docs.cython.org/src/quickstart/install.html</a>), before trying to install pySTEP.</p>\n<p>The easiest way to install Cython is:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-sh\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre>easy_install cython\n</pre></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"installation\">\n<h2>1.2.2. Installation<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#installation\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>To install pySTEP, you need to unpack the archive, enter the directory, and then run:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-sh\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre>python setup.py build_ext --inplace\npython setup.py install\n</pre></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"testing-the-installation\">\n<h2>1.2.3. Testing the Installation<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#testing-the-installation\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>After having install pySTEP, you can test it with:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-python\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">pystepx.tutorials.Tutorial</span>\n<span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">pystepx</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">tutorials</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tutorial</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tutorial1</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n", "display_toc": true, "title": "1.2. Installing pySTEP", "sourcename": "quickstart/install.txt", "current_page_name": "quickstart/install", "next": {"link": "../../tutorial/", "title": "2. Tutorials"}, "rellinks": [["genindex", "General Index", "I", "index"], ["modindex", "Global Module Index", "M", "modules"], ["tutorial/index", "2. Tutorials", "N", "next"], ["quickstart/overview", "1.1. pySTEP - an overview", "P", "previous"]], "meta": {}, "parents": [{"link": "../", "title": "1. Getting Started"}], "toc": "<ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#\">1.2. Installing pySTEP</a><ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#pre-requisite\">1.2.1. Pre-requisite</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#installation\">1.2.2. Installation</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#testing-the-installation\">1.2.3. Testing the Installation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n", "prev": {"link": "../overview/", "title": "1.1. pySTEP - an overview"}, "metatags": ""}